    {
      "id": "1525918360762712076",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2026-07-12T17:34:47.398+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "But, in theory, all you need to do is update the beginning of the input stimulus section to\n```\n*** 5. INPUT STIMULUS ***\nV_clk            clk            VSS PULSE( 0 3.3 0 0.1ns 0.1ns 50ns 200ns )\nV_clk_n          clk_n          VSS PULSE( 0 3.3 100ns 0.1ns 0.1ns 50ns 200ns )\nV_rst_n          rst_n          VSS PULSE( 0 3.3 375ns 0.1ns 0.1ns 5us 6us )\nV_rst_override_n rst_override_n VSS PULSE( 0 3.3 375ns 0.1ns 0.1ns 5us 6us )\n```\nAnd then run that for a few clock cycles and observe the outputs. This is set up for a 5us long run.",
      "author": {
        "id": "220639106915368960",
        "name": "tholin",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "Tholin",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
